The Grão-Pará Palace image is indeed not good, but the not may be said about the one of the Santa Cruz Estate. I'm also adding the Château d'Eu, which belonged and served as residence to the Brazilian Imperial amily from 1896, when it was inherited by the Count of Eu from his deceased father, the Duke of Nemours, until 1945, when they sold the castle to the entrepeneur Assis Chateaubriand.

The Grão-Pará Palace belongs to the Brazilian Imperial Family since it's construction as a guest's palace. The Santa Cruz estate belonged to King João VI, Emperors Pedro I and Pedro II as a private property.

Putting all notes in the "Notes" section for consistency. Uruguayan census term is "asiática o amarilla" or "Asian/yellow". The "Yellow" racial term refers to East Asians, like in [[Brazil]]'s census. Nothing's mentioned on how all of Asia is classified, as the term "[[yellow race]]" did not refer to every Asian ethnic group. And since the "yellow" racial term may be "confusing" or "outdated" to English-speakers, I'm adding a note for clarification.
